race.comment: INQUISITOR (4) shed the maiden tag at Ballina in dominant fashion last time out and will have derived a stack of confidence from that breakthrough victory. Gets a stack of weight off with the 3kg claim and should be right there at the business end. NORTY FORTY (7) just ran into one better at Eagle Farm at the latest outing and may have turned the corner now. Don't discount lightly. DUSHENKA (2) was a touch disappointing last start but the three runs prior to start the campaign were full of merit. Can bounce back without surprising. DIVERSITY (5) is one from one over this course and distance and must be respected out of the Freedman barn. In the mix on best form. POWER REECE (6) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on.
